RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 86. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 24000. FOR (REGISTERED BRED AND/OR FOALED IN ILLINOIS) THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER OR WAIVER CLAIMING OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING $12,500 FOR HORSES WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since June 23 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: THE LAST FACT was urged along to share the lead outside ST. LOUIE LOUIE, moved clear after two furlongs, saved ground through the bend and held sway under urging in the lane. ST. LOUIE LOUIE vied for the lead from inside, did not keep up after a quarter mile, was two wide on the turn, lugged in some to bump ANDTHETHUNDERROLLS with a sixteenth left, jostled with the latter through the waning yards and came up short for the win. ANDTHETHUNDERROLLS was settled inside, picked up his pace after two furlong, progressed along the rail, found himself boxed in behind THE LAST FACT in the stretch, was bumped with a sixteenth to go, altered out some in the late going, jostled with ST. LOUIE LOIUIE to the wire while finishing on even terms with that one. HIGHLY PERFECT soon trailed, was taken to the outside midway on the backstretch, widest through the bend and rallied belatedly in the lane. MAN ON ATTACK raced in contention from outside, was three wide taking the turn then flattened out for the drive.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 64. Claiming Purse 7500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $3,200.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COOKIN ROSES was urged to a clear lead and the inside, widened command on the bend, floated out some entering the lane, drifted out under left-handed pressure deep stretch but kept VIVA VIOLENCE at bay. VIVA VIOLENCE advanced from inside on the turn to move clear for second, fanned outside COOKIN ROSES into the stretch, gradually angled out as the latter came out in the late going and lacked the extra needed in the waning yards. TWO MORE TIMES chased from outside on the backstretch, progressed from inside on the bend, moved clear for third upper stretch then could only make up minor ground the last eighth. RANK AND FILE in contention early three wide, failed to keep up on the turn and rallied belatedly widest in the lane. DEAUVILLE MIST prominent just outside COOKIN ROSES from the early going, did not keep up on the bend, fanned out behind VIVA VIOLENCE entering the lane and also found best stride too late. BAILESTON LASSIE stayed well off the inside and showed little.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 3 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 71. Claiming Purse 7500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $3,200.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SUPERTRIX rated off the early speed, was three wide on the second bend, fanned out further entering the lane, was forced out some upper stretch, jostled repeatedly with GHAALEB'S DREAMS as those two were making their bid, gained a narrow advantage at the sixteenth marker then slowly edged ahead nearing the wire. CLOSE TO ME progressed from outside through the first turn, angled in some on the backstretch, was two wide taking the second turn, drifted out slightly once straightened in the stretch, dueled for the lead between rivals the final sixteenth but lacked the needed late kick. MARIA'S GIFT was a step slow then caught in tight quarters at the break, settled inside, angled out midway on the backstretch, lost ground widest through the second bend, drifted out some midstretch, rallied the final furlong and drifted out gradually through the waning yards. GHAALEB'S DREAMS raced in contention just off the rail, swung out to path three entering the lane, altered outside CLOSE TO ME at the top of the stretch, crowding SUPERTRIX, jostled repeatedly with that one as she made her bid and did not have enough nearing the finish. BOBBIE TOO TOO broke alertly and was quickly clear, showed the way in hand from inside, was challenged on the second turn, shook free upper stretch but gradually wore down in the late going. There was a stewards' inquiry into the jostling between SUPERTRIK and GHAALEB'S DREAMS in the stretch run. After their review, no action was taken.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 89. Claiming Purse 10500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since June 23 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250 (Claiming Races For $5,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MEDAL OF FACT was sent to share the early lead from outside, was two wide on the bend, took over as he drifted out to path six entering the lane, moved clear inside the last eighth, began to wear down the final sixteenth but kept D' YANK at bay. D' YANK chased from inside, swung out to path four into the stretch, surged inside the final furlong, gained second seventy yards out and came up short for the win. FULL MAGAZINE prominent behind the early speed, threatened three wide on the bend, was carried out by MEDAL OF FACT into the stretch and was drifting out in the waning yards. CREEKMORE was hustled along to dispute the pace from inside, lost the advantage as he floated out leaving the turn and gradually yielded for the drive. SONNYISNOTSOFUNNY forwardly placed from outside, improved position four wide on the bend, drifted out leaving leaving the turn and did not recover. GINSBURNED displayed early speed between horses but began to fade after three furlongs.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 5 6F Dirt CR: 55. Maiden Special Weight Purse 24500. FOR (REGISTERED BRED AND/OR FOALED IN ILLINOIS) MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: XPRESSIR crowded leaving the chute, moved clear midway on the backstretch, was roused with two furlongs to go, lengthened command upper stretch, bore out under left-handed pressure after entering the last eighth, held a straight path the final sixteenth and maintained full control. SPAN reluctant to load, was hustled along early, lost ground four to six wide through the bend, rallied through the lane, was too late but caught ITS MAMBO for second. ITS MAMBO chased from not far off the rail, waited for room behind a wall of horses approaching the end of a half mile, altered to the rail leaving the quarter pole, squeezed through to rallied in the stretch, had second inside the final furlong, leveled off in the late going but was easily best of the rest. GRAYHOP broke slowly and inward, saved ground taking the turn, altered out upper stretch and weaved in and out through traffic to advance the last eighth. SMOOTH ATTACK broke inward, was hustled along between rivals, moved clear for second just off the inside on the bend, floated out to path four into the lane, was no match for XPRESSIR and gave way the last eighth. FLYING CRICKET in midpack early, moved to the inside after two furlongs, squeezed through tight quarters between horses leaving the quarter pole, came three wide into the stretch and had no late bid. PONCHO ATTACK also in midpack early from outside, was three to five wide taking the turn and gave way for the drive. FAST KYLIE prominent early, failed to keep up along the rail on the bend, floated out some leaving the turn and quickly faded.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 6 1M Dirt CR: 81. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 16000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING 10,000 FOR HORSES THAT HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since June 23 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Claim ing Races For $7,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GOLD SMOKE settled early, commenced his bid after a half mile, reached contention four wide on the second bend, dueled for the lead outside PATH TO SUCCESS inside the final furlong, was bumped and jostled briefly with that one seventy yards out and edged ahead nearing the wire. PATH TO SUCCESS rated off the early speed, commenced his bid three wide on the second turn, engaged RABBIT HOUND upper stretch, battled between rivals inside the last eighth, drifted out with seventy yards to go, bumped GOLD SMOKE, jostled with that one briefly, fought gamely to the wire but had to settle for second. ARROW STRIKE prominent from inside, lost his path to RABBIT HOUND nearing the end of six furlongs, tried but failed to squeeze through inside PAYNT BY LETTERS leaving the quarter pole, lost his path just inside that one upper stretch, was steadied behind traffic inside the last furlong, altered outside GOLD SMOKE inside the final sixteenth, closed well but was too late. RABBIT HOUND was hustled to vie for the early lead inside rivals, was just off inside on the backstretch, moved ahead and took the rail midway on the second turn, was challenged upper stretch and slowly yielded in the waning yards. PLAIN OR PEANUT settled just off the inside, lodged his bid after a half mile, progressed widest through the second turn, ran evenly the last two furlongs but was easily best of the others. VALIENTE CLAYMORE failed to menace in a ground-saving trip. PAYNT BY LETTERS disputed the pace between horses, began to yield two wide on the second bend, floated out some into the lane and gave way. MINNESOTA MOON was hustled to contest the pace outside PAYNT BY LETTERS but gave way on the second turn.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 7 6F Dirt CR: 100. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 18000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD NON-WINNERS OF THREE RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, WAIVER CLAIMING, STARTER OR IBF OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FIVE RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE OF $15,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs. ; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since June 23 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000 (Claiming Races For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DEVIL'S TOWER shared the early lead inside rivals, was just off the rail on the bend, moved ahead under urging in the lane, gradually drifted out after entering the last furlong, held a straight path the final sixteenth and prevailed. PAPA ROCKET broke inward, was settled inside, waited for room just off the rail leaving the turn, got through three wide upper stretch, angled out some as DEVIL'S TOWER came out inside the final furlong, came up short at the end but caught HELA for second nearing the wire. HELA gradually progressed from inside to threaten with a furlong to go, leveled off instead but was clearly best of the others. W W CRAZY in contention early, failed to keep up three wide on the bend, passed a couple tired horses upper stretch then leveled off. SEMINOLE BEACH broke outward, bumping HUEY ATTACK, vied for the lead toward the outside, lost ground five then six wide through the turn, faded and drifted out midstretch. ONE PUTT RICHIE contested the pace between rivals, was in tight quarters on the bend, floated out slightly as he began to fade upper stretch, brushed with HUEY ATTACK, was altered in and continued to give way. HUEY ATTACK was bumped at the break, vied for the lead outside ONE PUTT RICHIE, did not keep up into the lane, was crowded briefly by the latter once straightened for the drive and also continued to fade.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 8 6F Dirt CR: 77. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 14000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD NON-WINNERS OF A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, WAIVER CLAIMING, STARTER OR IBF OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-w inners Of A Race Since June 23 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Claiming Races For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SALLY'S SUPRISE was sent to vie for the early lead, had the rail on the turn, floated out some entering the lane, drifted out briefly upper stretch as she drew off under urging, kept a straight path the last furlong and proved much the best. FREE LOVE contested the pace outside SALLY'S SUPRISE for a half mile, was no match for that one when set down for the drive but was unchallenged for the place. MAYSTART in contention early between rivals, failed to keep up along the rail on the bend, battled for third just off the inside deep stretch and got it late. GHAALEB'S RANGER soon trailed, was three wide on the turn, fanned out some for the drive and showed a willingness to run deep stretch between foes. DELTA LADY forwardly placed from inside on the backstretch, failed to stay close on the bend, swung out leaving the turn, came three wide into the lane, altered outside GHAALEB'S RANGER inside the last eighth and was making up ground on that one in the waning yards. FOGGY KITTEN pressed the early speed from just off the rail, angled out through the turn, was five wide entering the stretch and gradually wore down the final furlong. AWESOME SUNDAY flipped in the gate before the start, was taken out and given the okay to race from the veterinarian after examination, was an early contender from outside but gave way four wide on the bend.
